org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.components.modellibs.core.mappingrules

Class UseConjIntf

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.components.modellibs.core.mappingrules.UseConjIntf
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMappingRule

    public class UseConjIntf
extends Object
implements IMappingRule
    Use a conjugated interface (!= conjugated port), i.e. an interface in which the roles "in" and "out" of each parameter of an operation are inversed. This transformation is useful in the context of transforming a "push" interface into a "pull" interface, i.e. instead of calling and providing values values to the called component via "in", the called components queries us and obtains these values as out parameters. TODO: This rules is currently not used, since data flow operation are currently either based on a datatype or a MARTE FlowPort
